\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. M. caucasica} (Willd.) Poiret in Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot. Suppl.}{\b  3}: 604 (1814) ({\i T. caucasicum} (Willd.) Hayek). Perennial. Stems 15-50 cm, simple, subglabrous, erect or ascending from a short fibrous creeping rhizome. Leaves glabrous; lower cauline 4-7 × 1·5-2·5 cm, 2-pinnatisect into fairly long acute segments. Capitulum 1(-3), 3-5 cm in diameter; ligules 1·5-2 cm; involucral bracts narrowly triangular to oblong, with a wide, blackish-brown scarious margin. Achenes c. 2·5 × 1 mm; 1-2 slender supernumerary ribs often present; abaxial surface dark brown and smooth or somewhat rugose; resin-glands 2, small, orbicular; pappus 0·3-0·5 mm, pale, membranous, entire or somewhat lobed.{\i  Alpine meadows. Mountains of W. & C. Bulgaria and E. Albania}. Al Bu ?Ju. ({\i Caucasian region.})
\par

