\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. M. rosella} (Boiss. & Orph.) Nyman,{\i  Consp.} 374 (1879) ({\i T. rosellum} (Boiss. & Orph.) Hayek). Perennial. Stems 15-40 cm, subglabrous, ascending from a short rhizome, leafy only in lower 1/2-2/3. Leaves subglabrous; basal and lower cauline leaves 5-10 cm, pinnatisect only at base and in distal 1/4, with rhachis 0·7-1 mm wide extending for c. 2/3 of length of leaf; basal segments very narrow, pectinate and amplexicaul; distal segments 12-25, 0·5-1 cm, acute. Capitulum 1(-2), c. 2·5 cm in diameter; ligules c. 0·7 cm, pink; involucral bracts with a narrow pale brown scarious margin, the outer c. 4/5 as long as the inner. Achenes c. 2 mm; ribs pale and slightly separated; abaxial surface brown and somewhat rugose; resin-glands 2, of medium size, separate or laterally connate; pappus c. 0·4 mm.{\i  Mountain slopes,} c. 900{\i  m. S. Greece} ({\i Parnon Oros}). Gr.
